Module com.fy916.bubblebobble
Package com.fy916.bubblebobble.gaming.elements.movingelements

Class MovingObject

java.lang.Object
com.fy916.bubblebobble.gaming.elements.ObjectFeature
com.fy916.bubblebobble.gaming.elements.GameObject
com.fy916.bubblebobble.gaming.elements.movingelements.MovingObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
Bubble, Enemy, Fruit, Hero, Projectile, ScoreIndicator
public abstract class MovingObject extends GameObject
An abstract class which is extended from the GameObject, this is intended for the objects that will be moving around within the game world (unlinke MapObject).
This class contains some ability that the moving objects will have like velocity, acceleration, direction, Die, Jump, these properties shows the Stragety Design pattern.
Author:
fy916

    • MovingObject

      public MovingObject​(InteractableWorld world, int colNum, int rowNum, int objectwidth, int objectheight)
      Constructor that takes unit column and rows to initialize the object
      Parameters:
      world - current game world
      colNum - the column of location the unit in the game world, note this is not the exact coordinate but the relevant location of the objects without multiplying the unit size
      rowNum - the row of location the unit in the game world, note this is not the exact coordinate but the relevant location of the objects without multiplying the unit size
      objectheight - the height of the object
      objectwidth - the width of the object
